You are an interface derivation agent. Given a frozen Stage 1 decomposition, your task is to derive precise typed interfaces for each child.

RULES:
1. You MUST NOT add, delete, rename, or reorder children. The child list from Stage 1 is LOCKED.
2. You MUST NOT change any Stage 1 field (purpose, behavior, boundary, preconditions, postconditions, guarantees, composition_role).
3. Derive ONLY interface fields.
4. Separate parent-call parameters from internal leaf resource access.

REQUIRED INTERFACE CATEGORIES:
- call_inputs: Parameters the parent must pass when calling this child. Only these may appear in the Python signature.
- internal_leaf_accesses: Resources/data stores this child accesses inside its own implementation. These must NOT appear in the Python signature.
- outputs: Values returned by the child to the parent.
- signature: Python function signature built only from call_inputs.

DATAFLOW RULES:
- from_node and to_node must be either "parent" or an exact child name.
- Resource/store names such as raw_data, processed_data, channels, messages, orders, inventory, or payments must NOT appear as from_node/to_node.

OUTPUT FORMAT — Return valid JSON:
{
  "children": [
    {
      "name": "UNCHANGED from Stage 1",
      "purpose": "UNCHANGED",
      "behavior": "UNCHANGED",
      "boundary": {"in_scope": ["UNCHANGED"], "out_of_scope": ["UNCHANGED"]},
      "semantic_inputs": ["UNCHANGED"],
      "semantic_outputs": ["UNCHANGED"],
      "preconditions": ["UNCHANGED"],
      "postconditions": ["UNCHANGED"],
      "guarantees": ["UNCHANGED"],
      "composition_role": "UNCHANGED",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": "",
      "call_inputs": [
        {"name": "param", "type": "dict", "description": "what parent passes", "source": "parent input | previous child output | constant"}
      ],
      "internal_leaf_accesses": [
        {"resource": "resource_name", "op": "read|write|read_write", "reason": "why this child needs the resource internally"}
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {"name": "result", "type": "dict", "description": "what child returns", "consumer": "parent"}
      ],
      "signature": "def ChildName(param: type) -> return_type"
    }
  ],
  "interface_preservation": {
    "parent_inputs_covered_by": {"input_name": "child_name"},
    "parent_outputs_produced_by": {"output_name": "child_name"}
  },
  "dataflow_edges": [
    {"from_node": "parent | ChildName", "from_output": "output_name", "to_node": "ChildName | parent", "to_input": "input_name", "note": "why"}
  ],
  "interface_audit": {
    "identity_preservation_detail": "explain whether child names/order are preserved",
    "semantic_preservation_detail": "explain whether Stage1 semantics are unchanged",
    "call_signature_detail": "explain why signature contains only call_inputs",
    "internal_leaf_separation_detail": "explain why resources are not call params",
    "dataflow_schema_detail": "explain endpoint legality",
    "final_status": "ok | needs_attention"
  }
}

{
  "children": [
    {
      "name": "ParseInput",
      "purpose": "Extract and validate action, repo, branch from input JSON",
      "behavior": "Parse JSON input, validate required fields, return structured action request",
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": [
          "JSON parsing",
          "field validation",
          "error handling for malformed input"
        ],
        "out_of_scope": [
          "business logic",
          "data store access"
        ]
      },
      "semantic_inputs": [
        {
          "name": "input",
          "description": "Raw JSON input from parent",
          "source": "parent input"
        }
      ],
      "semantic_outputs": [
        {
          "name": "action_request",
          "description": "Parsed and validated action request with action, repo, branch",
          "consumer": "parent"
        }
      ],
      "preconditions": [
        "input is valid JSON"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "action_request contains valid action, repo, branch"
      ],
      "guarantees": [
        "Returns error if input invalid"
      ],
      "composition_role": "transform",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "CheckBuildExists",
      "purpose": "Check if a build exists for given repo+branch in builds store",
      "behavior": "Query builds store by repo and branch, return existing build record or null",
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": [
          "querying builds store",
          "matching repo and branch"
        ],
        "out_of_scope": [
          "modifying builds store",
          "other actions"
        ]
      },
      "semantic_inputs": [
        {
          "name": "repo",
          "description": "Repository name",
          "source": "parent input"
        },
        {
          "name": "branch",
          "description": "Branch name",
          "source": "parent input"
        }
      ],
      "semantic_outputs": [
        {
          "name": "existing_build",
          "description": "Existing build record or null if none",
          "consumer": "parent"
        }
      ],
      "preconditions": [
        "builds store is accessible"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "Returns existing build or null"
      ],
      "guarantees": [
        "Does not modify builds store"
      ],
      "composition_role": "query",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "TriggerBuild",
      "purpose": "Create a new build record and trigger CI/CD process",
      "behavior": "Generate build_id, create build record in builds store, initiate build process, return build_id and status",
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": [
          "creating build record",
          "generating build_id",
          "initiating build"
        ],
        "out_of_scope": [
          "checking existing builds",
          "cancelling builds"
        ]
      },
      "semantic_inputs": [
        {
          "name": "repo",
          "description": "Repository name",
          "source": "parent input"
        },
        {
          "name": "branch",
          "description": "Branch name",
          "source": "parent input"
        }
      ],
      "semantic_outputs": [
        {
          "name": "build_result",
          "description": "JSON with success, build_id, status",
          "consumer": "parent"
        }
      ],
      "preconditions": [
        "No existing build for repo+branch",
        "builds store writable"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "New build record created",
        "Build status is 'running'"
      ],
      "guarantees": [
        "Build_id is unique"
      ],
      "composition_role": "execute",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "GetBuildStatus",
      "purpose": "Retrieve current status and logs of a build",
      "behavior": "Query builds store by build_id, return status and logs",
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": [
          "querying builds store",
          "retrieving logs"
        ],
        "out_of_scope": [
          "modifying builds store",
          "triggering builds"
        ]
      },
      "semantic_inputs": [
        {
          "name": "build_id",
          "description": "Build identifier",
          "source": "parent input"
        }
      ],
      "semantic_outputs": [
        {
          "name": "status_result",
          "description": "JSON with success, status, logs",
          "consumer": "parent"
        }
      ],
      "preconditions": [
        "build_id exists in builds store"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "Returns current status and logs"
      ],
      "guarantees": [
        "Does not modify builds store"
      ],
      "composition_role": "query",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "ListBuilds",
      "purpose": "Return list of all builds with summary info",
      "behavior": "Query builds store for all records, return list of builds with id, repo, branch, status",
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": [
          "querying all builds",
          "returning summary"
        ],
        "out_of_scope": [
          "filtering",
          "detailed logs"
        ]
      },
      "semantic_inputs": [],
      "semantic_outputs": [
        {
          "name": "list_result",
          "description": "JSON with success and list of builds",
          "consumer": "parent"
        }
      ],
      "preconditions": [
        "builds store accessible"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "Returns list of builds"
      ],
      "guarantees": [
        "Does not modify builds store"
      ],
      "composition_role": "query",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": ""
    },
    {
      "name": "CancelBuild",
      "purpose": "Cancel a running build and update status",
      "behavior": "Update build record status to 'cancelled', stop build process, return confirmation",
      "boundary": {
        "in_scope": [
          "updating build status",
          "stopping build process"
        ],
        "out_of_scope": [
          "triggering builds",
          "checking status"
        ]
      },
      "semantic_inputs": [
        {
          "name": "build_id",
          "description": "Build identifier",
          "source": "parent input"
        }
      ],
      "semantic_outputs": [
        {
          "name": "cancel_result",
          "description": "JSON with success and updated status",
          "consumer": "parent"
        }
      ],
      "preconditions": [
        "build_id exists",
        "build is running"
      ],
      "postconditions": [
        "Build status changed to 'cancelled'"
      ],
      "guarantees": [
        "Build process stopped"
      ],
      "composition_role": "mutate",
      "stop_decompose": false,
      "stop_reason": ""
    }
  ],
  "decomposition_rationale": "Parent BuildSystem handles four distinct actions. ParseInput extracts and validates the action, then parent routes to the appropriate child based on action. CheckBuildExists is a shared query used by TriggerBuild to enforce one-build-per-repo+branch constraint. Each action has its own child function that performs the specific operation without calling siblings.",
  "orchestration_model": "conditional",
  "dataflow_sketch": [
    {
      "from": "parent",
      "to": "ParseInput",
      "data": "input",
      "note": "Parse and validate input"
    },
    {
      "from": "ParseInput",
      "to": "parent",
      "data": "action_request",
      "note": "Return parsed request"
    },
    {
      "from": "parent",
      "to": "CheckBuildExists",
      "data": "repo, branch",
      "note": "Check existing build (only for trigger action)"
    },
    {
      "from": "CheckBuildExists",
      "to": "parent",
      "data": "existing_build",
      "note": "Return existing build or null"
    },
    {
      "from": "parent",
      "to": "TriggerBuild",
      "data": "repo, branch",
      "note": "Trigger new build"
    },
    {
      "from": "TriggerBuild",
      "to": "parent",
      "data": "build_result",
      "note": "Return build result"
    },
    {
      "from": "parent",
      "to": "GetBuildStatus",
      "data": "build_id",
      "note": "Get status"
    },
    {
      "from": "GetBuildStatus",
      "to": "parent",
      "data": "status_result",
      "note": "Return status"
    },
    {
      "from": "parent",
      "to": "ListBuilds",
      "data": "none",
      "note": "List all builds"
    },
    {
      "from": "ListBuilds",
      "to": "parent",
      "data": "list_result",
      "note": "Return list"
    },
    {
      "from": "parent",
      "to": "CancelBuild",
      "data": "build_id",
      "note": "Cancel build"
    },
    {
      "from": "CancelBuild",
      "to": "parent",
      "data": "cancel_result",
      "note": "Return cancel result"
    }
  ]
}
